# Component System Guide

Standards for building, naming, organizing, and documenting UI components
in the {{PROJECT_NAME}} design system.

---

## Template Variables

- `{{PROJECT_NAME}}` -- Project name
- `{{COMPONENT_PREFIX}}` -- Optional prefix for domain components (e.g., `tms`, `crm`)
- `{{FRONTEND_FRAMEWORK}}` -- UI framework: `react` | `next` | `vue` | `svelte`
- `{{CSS_FRAMEWORK}}` -- Styling approach: `tailwind` | `css-modules` | `styled-components`

---

## 1. Naming Conventions

### File Naming

| Type            | Pattern                          | Example                          |
|-----------------|----------------------------------|----------------------------------|
| Shared UI       | `PascalCase.tsx`                 | `Button.tsx`, `DataTable.tsx`    |
| Domain-specific | `PascalCase.tsx` in domain dir   | `LoadCard.tsx`, `CarrierBadge.tsx` |
| Story           | `ComponentName.stories.tsx`      | `Button.stories.tsx`             |
| Test            | `ComponentName.test.tsx`         | `Button.test.tsx`                |
| Types           | `ComponentName.types.ts`         | `DataTable.types.ts`             |
| Hooks           | `use-feature-name.ts`            | `use-debounce.ts`                |

### Component Naming Rules

- PascalCase for all component names
- Noun-first for data display: `LoadCard`, `CarrierTable`, `InvoiceList`
- Verb-first for actions: `CreateLoadDialog`, `EditCarrierForm`
- Suffix patterns:
  - `*Card` -- summary display in a card
  - `*Table` -- tabular data display
  - `*List` -- vertical list display
  - `*Form` -- data input form
  - `*Dialog` -- modal dialog
  - `*Badge` -- inline status indicator
  - `*Layout` -- page layout wrapper
  - `*Provider` -- context provider

