## 6. Accessibility Requirements

### Per Component Type

| Component Type | Requirements |
|----------------|-------------|
| **Button**     | `role="button"`, keyboard activation (Enter/Space), visible focus ring, `disabled` + `aria-disabled`, loading state announced |
| **Input**      | Associated `<label>`, `aria-describedby` for help/error text, `aria-invalid` for errors, `required` attribute |
| **Dialog**     | `role="dialog"`, `aria-labelledby`, `aria-describedby`, focus trap, Escape to close, return focus on close |
| **Select**     | `role="listbox"`, arrow key navigation, typeahead search, `aria-expanded`, `aria-selected` |
| **Table**      | `role="table"`, `<th scope="col/row">`, sortable headers with `aria-sort`, caption or `aria-label` |
| **Badge/Tag**  | Informational: no role needed. Interactive: `role="button"`, focusable. Status: text label always present (not color alone) |
| **Toast**      | `role="alert"` or `role="status"`, `aria-live="polite"`, auto-dismiss with adequate time (5s+) |
| **Tabs**       | `role="tablist"`, `role="tab"`, `role="tabpanel"`, arrow key navigation, `aria-selected` |
| **Sidebar**    | `<nav>` element, `aria-label`, `aria-current="page"` for active link |

### Universal Requirements

1. **Focus visible:** All interactive elements must show a visible focus ring (`focus-visible:ring-2 ring-ring`)
2. **Color not alone:** Never convey information through color alone -- always pair with text, icon, or pattern
3. **Keyboard navigable:** Every interactive element reachable and operable via keyboard
4. **Screen reader text:** Use `sr-only` class for visually hidden but announced text
5. **Reduced motion:** Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` for animations
6. **Touch targets:** Minimum 44x44px for touch targets on mobile

### Testing Accessibility

- Use `@storybook/addon-a11y` for automated checks in Storybook
- Run axe-core in CI (`jest-axe` or `@axe-core/playwright`)
- Manual testing: keyboard-only navigation, screen reader (NVDA/VoiceOver)
